Uses of Interface
gui.GraphElement

  • Packages that use GraphElement 
    Package Description
    gui
    The graphical user interface for the shortest paths algorithm (you don't need to look at or understand this package, but you can run it to play with the gui).

    • Uses of GraphElement in gui

      Classes in gui that implement GraphElement 
      Modifier and Type Class Description
      class  EdgeData
      Class Edge allows creation of connections between Nodes.
      Each Edge is bidirectional and is connected to exactly two Nodes.
      class  NodeData
      A Node (vertex) of the graph.
      Constructors in gui with parameters of type GraphElement 
      Constructor Description
      Circle​(GraphElement r, int x, int y, int d)
      Constructor: an instance at (x, y) of diameter d and colored black
      that represents r and is not filled.
      Circle​(GraphElement r, int x, int y, int d, java.awt.Color c, boolean filled)
      Constructor: an instance at (x, y) of diameter d and colored c
      that represents r and is filled iff filled.
      DraggableCircle​(GraphElement r, int x, int y, int d)
      Constructor: an instance at (x, y) of diameter d that represents piece r.
      Line​(Circle c1, Circle c2, GraphElement r)
      Constructor: a line from c1 to c2 representing r and colored black.
